description: Wolfblood is a British fantasy/supernatural television series aimed at teens. It is a co-production between CBBC and ZDF/ZDFE. The series focuses on teenage wolfbloods Madeline 'Maddy' Smith (Aimee Kelly) and Rhydian Morris (Bobby Lockwood) as they struggle living their double lives as wolfbloods and keeping their secret concealed from the outside world, including their friends. Wolfblood premiered on CBBC on 10 September 2012, and premiered on Disney Channel in the United States on 1 October 2013. A second series was broadcast on CBBC in September and October 2013. Series 3 ended on 27 October 2014
